WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.335 --> 00:00:02.335
Hello.

2
00:00:02.803 --> 00:00:04.863
Yates chooses his
victims at random.

3
00:00:05.339 --> 00:00:07.501
<i>Nadia Decotis was
tortured and killed.</i>

4
00:00:07.608 --> 00:00:09.941
<i>Yates transported
her to his burial ground.</i>

5
00:00:10.444 --> 00:00:11.444
RAFAEL: How many others?

6
00:00:11.512 --> 00:00:12.512
VOIGHT: Seven so far.

7
00:00:12.579 --> 00:00:14.707
No forensics. nothing
to tie him to any of them?

8
00:00:14.882 --> 00:00:17.078
BENSON: <i>Green nail
polish was applied to victims.</i>

9
00:00:17.184 --> 00:00:19.085
<i>He either burned the
bodies or he buried them.</i>

10
00:00:19.353 --> 00:00:21.982
He gets off on
torture. even in court.

11
00:00:23.724 --> 00:00:25.955
You see what we saw?
Just hope the jury saw it.

12
00:00:26.059 --> 00:00:28.551
On the charge of murder
in the First Degree.

13
00:00:28.662 --> 00:00:31.996
we find the defendant.
Gregory Yates. guilty.

14
00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:41.240
NARRATOR: <i>In the
criminal justice system.</i>

15
00:00:41.441 --> 00:00:44.468
<i>sexually-based offenses are
considered especially heinous.</i>

16
00:00:45.145 --> 00:00:46.306
<i>In New York City.</i>

17
00:00:46.413 --> 00:00:49.315
<i>the dedicated detectives who
investigate these vicious felonies</i>

18
00:00:49.416 --> 00:00:52.580
<i>are members of an elite squad
known as the Special Victims Unit.</i>

19
00:00:52.686 --> 00:00:54.314
<i>These are their stories.</i>

20
00:01:18.478 --> 00:01:21.004
Was she dismembered or did
she come apart in the water?

21
00:01:21.114 --> 00:01:23.914
No obvious tears. But there are
cutting marks in the bones and tendons.

22
00:01:24.017 --> 00:01:26.714
Another body here at
Yates' burial ground.

23
00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:28.311
Yeah. some
skinny-dipping teenagers

24
00:01:28.422 --> 00:01:29.856
ditching class
kicked up the vic.

25
00:01:29.957 --> 00:01:31.267
Local precinct gave
us the heads-up.

26
00:01:31.291 --> 00:01:32.535
Thought it might
be one we missed.

27
00:01:32.559 --> 00:01:34.323
How? We covered
the whole island.

28
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:37.140
And Yates buried his bodies. This
one we found floating in the water.

29
00:01:37.164 --> 00:01:38.675
Just happens to coincide
with when and where

30
00:01:38.699 --> 00:01:39.860
Yates dumped Nadia Rollins.

31
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:42.469
Okay. What? He buried
Nadia. goes back out to Queens.

32
00:01:42.569 --> 00:01:44.265
assaults two flight attendants.

33
00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:47.602
has lunch with his fiancée. and finds
time for a fourth assault? Come on.

34
00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:49.473
The man was on a spree.

35
00:01:49.676 --> 00:01:52.840
For brunettes. She's a
redhead. It's not his type.

36
00:01:52.946 --> 00:01:56.815
We got nine dead bodies
found here. all by the same killer.

37
00:01:56.917 --> 00:01:58.818
And now we got the
tenth. Occam's razor.

38
00:01:58.919 --> 00:02:00.046
Enough. Guys. listen.

39
00:02:00.687 --> 00:02:03.247
We have two options. one is
bad. the other one is worse.

40
00:02:04.024 --> 00:02:07.722
Either we missed one.
or Yates has a copycat.

41
00:02:10.163 --> 00:02:13.725
Victim is a Caucasian
female. late 20s.

42
00:02:13.967 --> 00:02:16.596
Probable cause of
death. fractured skull.

43
00:02:17.671 --> 00:02:20.266
Right arm severed
surgically at the shoulder.

44
00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:23.804
Dr. Rudnick. are
we interrupting?

45
00:02:23.910 --> 00:02:26.539
No. not at all. Just
notating my initial findings.

46
00:02:27.014 --> 00:02:28.983
Found in Pelham Bay.

47
00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:34.417
so either she floated up as the water
warmed or CSU missed her in April?

48
00:02:34.521 --> 00:02:35.887
So you think Yates did this?

49
00:02:36.256 --> 00:02:38.521
I can't say definitively.

50
00:02:39.526 --> 00:02:43.054
But there are findings
consistent with Yates' MO.

51
00:02:43.597 --> 00:02:47.466
as well as evidence of injury. both
vaginal and anal. consistent with rape.

52
00:02:47.567 --> 00:02:49.593
Even after this
long in the water?

53
00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:51.671
There's no question
the skull was fractured.

54
00:02:52.039 --> 00:02:54.804
just like those of the two
flight attendants and Nadia.

55
00:02:54.908 --> 00:02:58.140
Yeah. but this body was also
dismembered. That's not part of Yates' MO.

56
00:02:58.245 --> 00:02:59.713
Correct. However. I can tell you

57
00:02:59.813 --> 00:03:01.893
the cuts were made by
someone with surgical training.

58
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:03.775
Uh. and another
interesting detail.

59
00:03:03.884 --> 00:03:07.719
microscopic traces of green
nail polish under two fingernails.

60
00:03:08.822 --> 00:03:10.051
Another coincidence. Rollins?

61
00:03:10.157 --> 00:03:11.157
It's public record.

62
00:03:11.258 --> 00:03:12.317
If you say so.

63
00:03:24.371 --> 00:03:25.964
Ooh. (SIGHS)

64
00:03:26.073 --> 00:03:27.837
That poor. poor girl.

65
00:03:28.942 --> 00:03:30.308
Raped. tortured.

66
00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:32.174
And her skull was fractured.

67
00:03:32.913 --> 00:03:34.541
You think I'm responsible?

68
00:03:35.982 --> 00:03:38.747
I understand. It is
the logical assumption.

69
00:03:39.052 --> 00:03:40.816
We had a saying
in medical school.

70
00:03:40.921 --> 00:03:44.653
"If you hear hoof beats.
think horses. not zebras."

71
00:03:45.325 --> 00:03:49.421
The ME found traces of
green polish on her fingernails.

72
00:03:50.864 --> 00:03:52.025
Really?

73
00:03:54.901 --> 00:03:56.733
Now that is fascinating.

74
00:03:59.539 --> 00:04:01.872
Someone committed
this horrific crime

75
00:04:02.209 --> 00:04:03.677
and then he went out of his way

76
00:04:03.777 --> 00:04:06.246
to piggyback it onto
crimes I've been accused of.

77
00:04:06.346 --> 00:04:09.180
That was my initial response.

78
00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:10.341
And the red hair...

79
00:04:10.450 --> 00:04:11.450
(SCOFFS)

80
00:04:11.551 --> 00:04:14.885
Gingers are anathema to me.

81
00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:16.288
I prefer brunettes.

82
00:04:16.356 --> 00:04:17.517
No offense.

83
00:04:17.858 --> 00:04:19.349
It's a long story.

84
00:04:19.459 --> 00:04:22.361
And the body. dismembered...

85
00:04:22.462 --> 00:04:24.761
It's so unnecessary.

86
00:04:24.865 --> 00:04:26.060
It's so barbaric.

87
00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.495
Well. any ideas why
somebody would have done it?

88
00:04:28.769 --> 00:04:30.465
Well. I don't know.

89
00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:35.133
Maybe the killer likes the act
of cutting into bone and flesh.

90
00:04:35.242 --> 00:04:37.143
Do you mind if I...

91
00:04:37.878 --> 00:04:39.346
Have another look?

92
00:04:39.546 --> 00:04:40.673
Go right ahead.

93
00:04:44.251 --> 00:04:45.251
Mmm-hmm.

94
00:04:56.196 --> 00:04:57.255
I'm really sorry.

95
00:04:57.364 --> 00:04:58.457
You...

96
00:04:58.565 --> 00:05:00.397
You have your
work cut out for you.

97
00:05:09.543 --> 00:05:11.205
I appreciate your help. Doctor.

98
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:19.279
Thoughts are occurring.

99
00:05:20.387 --> 00:05:23.653
If I can. uh. stew on
them for a couple of days.

100
00:05:25.125 --> 00:05:27.185
I might have something for you.

101
00:05:29.930 --> 00:05:31.296
(DOOR BUZZES OPEN)

102
00:05:36.136 --> 00:05:37.160
(DOOR LOCKS)

103
00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:42.509
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

104
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.218
Yates told you that
it wasn't him? Yeah.

105
00:06:28.321 --> 00:06:29.932
I bet he still says
that Nadia wasn't him.

106
00:06:29.956 --> 00:06:31.390
But the timeline is too tight.

107
00:06:31.491 --> 00:06:33.357
This girl was a redhead. okay?

108
00:06:33.460 --> 00:06:35.429
He's never dismembered
a body before this.

109
00:06:35.528 --> 00:06:37.053
We found skulls
last time. Amanda.

110
00:06:37.163 --> 00:06:39.242
Yeah. but that was skeletal
remains of decomped corpses.

111
00:06:39.266 --> 00:06:40.266
This is different.

112
00:06:40.367 --> 00:06:41.811
You know. his victims
were never prostitutes.

113
00:06:41.835 --> 00:06:42.928
this girl is a Jane Doe.

114
00:06:43.036 --> 00:06:44.937
Amanda. I don't know
what you're doing.

115
00:06:45.038 --> 00:06:46.336
but this isn't police work.

116
00:06:46.439 --> 00:06:47.907
I am cultivating a source.

117
00:06:48.008 --> 00:06:50.253
Listen. Yates hinted that he
might know who the killer is.

118
00:06:50.277 --> 00:06:51.609
Hinted. but didn't say?

119
00:06:51.811 --> 00:06:52.889
So what. you have
to go back there again.

120
00:06:52.913 --> 00:06:53.913
and then he'll tell you?

121
00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:56.040
He's playing you. This
guy's a psychopath.

122
00:06:56.149 --> 00:06:57.460
Not to mention. Amanda.
you went up there

123
00:06:57.484 --> 00:06:58.561
without clearing it with me.

124
00:06:58.585 --> 00:07:00.713
I'm not trusting your
judgment right now.

125
00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:03.551
Okay. All right. maybe
you guys are right.

126
00:07:03.657 --> 00:07:06.183
So say it is Yates. Just let
me keep building a rapport.

127
00:07:06.293 --> 00:07:08.319
Then maybe we can
finally get an ID on this girl.

128
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:09.428
(KNOCKING)

129
00:07:09.496 --> 00:07:10.862
Hey. Sarge. sorry to interrupt.

130
00:07:10.964 --> 00:07:12.404
but I finally got a
hit from our DNA.

131
00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:13.966
BENSON: From CODIS?

132
00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:17.334
No. military database. Vic's
name is Brooke Groves. 28.

133
00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:18.962
She was ROTC at
SUNY Plattsburgh.

134
00:07:19.072 --> 00:07:20.973
FIN: Didn't the ME say
she was a working girl?

135
00:07:21.107 --> 00:07:22.852
Well. yeah. but before
that. she had another life.

136
00:07:22.876 --> 00:07:24.310
Last known address
is in Larchmont.

137
00:07:24.411 --> 00:07:25.435
I'll go with.

138
00:07:25.578 --> 00:07:27.410
Actually. Rollins.
you stay here with Fin.

139
00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:30.617
I'll let you know
what we find out.

140
00:07:36.589 --> 00:07:37.648
There you are.

141
00:07:38.425 --> 00:07:40.503
Yeah. They spend all this
money renovating the squad room.

142
00:07:40.527 --> 00:07:41.807
and there's still
nothing to eat.

143
00:07:42.228 --> 00:07:43.389
How you feeling?

144
00:07:43.897 --> 00:07:46.162
I'm just tired.

145
00:07:46.266 --> 00:07:48.177
I've been taking too
many shifts since Nick left.

146
00:07:48.201 --> 00:07:49.499
You talk to him?

147
00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:53.563
(SIGHS) Yeah. Yeah. he's happy.

148
00:07:54.074 --> 00:07:56.634
He's. uh. doing physical
therapy in Laguna Beach.

149
00:07:56.743 --> 00:07:59.269
And he's got some kind of lead
with the US Park Police. so...

150
00:07:59.846 --> 00:08:02.145
You miss him. Is that
what this is all about?

151
00:08:02.615 --> 00:08:05.551
No. I'm pissed off. man.

152
00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:07.553
I get grounded
and this is my case.

153
00:08:07.654 --> 00:08:10.021
I mean. I know more about how
Yates thinks than Carisi does.

154
00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:11.830
Olivia's just looking
out for you. Amanda.

155
00:08:11.891 --> 00:08:13.587
Yeah. How do you figure?

156
00:08:15.195 --> 00:08:17.824
You're good at getting
inside these guys' heads.

157
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:22.059
Don't let 'em get inside yours.

158
00:08:31.444 --> 00:08:34.278
SONNY: Oh. no. Bikes.
toys? She's a mom.

159
00:08:34.381 --> 00:08:35.815
BENSON: No. they're not hers.

160
00:08:35.915 --> 00:08:38.749
If a mom disappears. they
file a missing persons report.

161
00:08:40.220 --> 00:08:41.313
(DOORBELL DINGS)

162
00:08:46.493 --> 00:08:47.493
Can I help you?

163
00:08:47.594 --> 00:08:48.823
Uh. yeah. we're NYPD.

164
00:08:48.928 --> 00:08:50.897
Um. Manhattan
Special Victims Unit.

165
00:08:50.997 --> 00:08:52.829
We're looking for
a Brooke Groves?

166
00:08:52.932 --> 00:08:54.127
That's me.

167
00:08:54.601 --> 00:08:56.729
Actually. it was me.
I'm Brooke Norwalk now.

168
00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:02.936
Hey. Tommy. Bobby.
go play on the iPad.

169
00:09:07.781 --> 00:09:09.301
Did something happen
to my husband? No.

170
00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:12.352
No. No. no. no. Um. we thought
something happened to you.

171
00:09:12.819 --> 00:09:14.048
I don't understand.

172
00:09:14.821 --> 00:09:16.380
It must have been a mistake.

173
00:09:16.489 --> 00:09:18.458
But we got a body in
the morgue. actually.

174
00:09:21.261 --> 00:09:22.923
Oh. no.

175
00:09:24.264 --> 00:09:28.929
Rachel. My twin sister.

176
00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:32.238
Are you still in touch with her?

177
00:09:32.939 --> 00:09:35.932
Off and on. My husband
doesn't know that.

178
00:09:37.077 --> 00:09:38.443
The boys have never even...

179
00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:41.347
After they were
born. my husband.

180
00:09:41.448 --> 00:09:43.349
he said she couldn't
come around anymore.

181
00:09:44.717 --> 00:09:46.310
She had problems?

182
00:09:47.821 --> 00:09:50.017
Rachel went to pieces
after our mom died.

183
00:09:50.190 --> 00:09:51.488
Drinking. drugs.

184
00:09:51.825 --> 00:09:54.106
She'd call me from the city.
swear she was gonna get help.

185
00:09:54.961 --> 00:09:57.055
I'd go into the city
and give her money.

186
00:09:58.898 --> 00:10:01.993
A few months ago.
she called again.

187
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:03.126
really high.

188
00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:06.105
and I told her I was
done enabling her.

189
00:10:09.409 --> 00:10:10.409
(EXHALES)

190
00:10:11.911 --> 00:10:12.935
How...

191
00:10:15.648 --> 00:10:17.310
What happened to my sister?

192
00:10:19.652 --> 00:10:23.180
I ran the DNA again. You
two were identical twins. yes?

193
00:10:23.656 --> 00:10:24.988
That's right.

194
00:10:25.091 --> 00:10:26.684
When we were
young. we... (SNIFFS)

195
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:27.793
Used to dress alike.

196
00:10:28.528 --> 00:10:30.019
No one could tell us apart.

197
00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:33.156
RUDNICK: Brace yourself.
There's significant decomposition.

198
00:10:33.266 --> 00:10:34.266
(SHUTTER OPENING)

199
00:10:36.903 --> 00:10:37.903
(GASPS)

200
00:10:40.340 --> 00:10:41.899
(CRYING) That's Rachel.

201
00:10:44.043 --> 00:10:46.069
(CRYING)

202
00:10:50.083 --> 00:10:51.745
I'm very sorry for your loss.

203
00:10:52.952 --> 00:10:53.952
(BROOKE SOBBING)

204
00:11:01.261 --> 00:11:02.695
SARITA: Rachel Groves.

205
00:11:02.795 --> 00:11:05.321
She stayed here on and
off. She was murdered?

206
00:11:05.465 --> 00:11:08.025
Yeah. We think she was targeted
because she was on the fringes.

207
00:11:08.201 --> 00:11:09.794
FIN: Somebody who
wouldn't be missed.

208
00:11:09.969 --> 00:11:11.494
Rachel was troubled.

209
00:11:11.604 --> 00:11:13.764
That's why I was so happy
when her mother came for her.

210
00:11:13.806 --> 00:11:14.865
"Mother"?

211
00:11:14.974 --> 00:11:16.135
I think it was her mother.

212
00:11:16.242 --> 00:11:18.871
The last time I saw Rachel.
she left with an older woman.

213
00:11:19.412 --> 00:11:20.971
Gray hair. nicely dressed.

214
00:11:21.114 --> 00:11:22.114
When was this?

215
00:11:22.215 --> 00:11:25.982
I'd have to check. It was
still cold. March. April.

216
00:11:26.653 --> 00:11:29.782
I remember the woman
had a long coat and a hat on.

217
00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:32.067
Okay. do you have
security cameras here?

218
00:11:32.091 --> 00:11:33.855
Yes. Come. follow me.

219
00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:43.665
So Rachel was last seen with
this woman. Can the sister ID her?

220
00:11:43.836 --> 00:11:45.998
Uh. no. I mean. their
mother died 10 years ago.

221
00:11:46.105 --> 00:11:48.284
And Brooke doesn't know any
other female relatives or friends.

222
00:11:48.308 --> 00:11:49.606
So who is she?

223
00:11:49.842 --> 00:11:51.208
Obviously not Yates.

224
00:11:51.811 --> 00:11:55.543
And look at the time code.
April 15th. Yates was in custody.

225
00:11:55.648 --> 00:11:58.243
April 15th. 2012.
That's three years off.

226
00:11:58.384 --> 00:11:59.682
Yeah and obviously it's a.m..

227
00:11:59.786 --> 00:12:01.730
but it reads as 11:30 p.m.
The time code was glitched.

228
00:12:01.754 --> 00:12:02.834
Okay. so check the machine.

229
00:12:02.889 --> 00:12:04.800
see what it reads now.
and then adjust it from there.

230
00:12:04.824 --> 00:12:05.951
No. I tried that.

231
00:12:06.059 --> 00:12:08.204
They already reset it once
they realized it was out of whack.

232
00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:09.719
I'll have TARU take a look.

233
00:12:11.564 --> 00:12:15.501
And. Sergeant. So in the
meantime. Yates called me. Twice.

234
00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:17.427
He says he has more information.

235
00:12:17.537 --> 00:12:19.028
He won't talk to anybody but me.

236
00:12:20.373 --> 00:12:23.070
Go. But not by yourself.

237
00:12:28.881 --> 00:12:29.974
(DOOR BUZZES)

238
00:12:31.517 --> 00:12:32.517
(LOCK CLICKS)

239
00:12:35.822 --> 00:12:38.417
You... You brought backup.

240
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:41.618
I thought this was gonna
be just between me and you.

241
00:12:41.728 --> 00:12:42.787
You thought wrong.

242
00:12:42.895 --> 00:12:44.573
We're here because
we were able to identify

243
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:45.860
the victim from Pelham Bay.

244
00:12:46.065 --> 00:12:47.465
You know. I already told you

245
00:12:47.567 --> 00:12:49.695
that I had nothing to do
with that girl. Mmm-hmm.

246
00:12:49.802 --> 00:12:51.930
You also told me that
you would stew on this.

247
00:12:52.038 --> 00:12:54.633
that you might be able to
come up with more information.

248
00:12:54.841 --> 00:12:56.571
Besides. it turns out

249
00:12:56.676 --> 00:12:58.076
she had a twin sister.

250
00:12:59.212 --> 00:13:01.044
It sure would mean
a lot to someone

251
00:13:01.147 --> 00:13:02.445
if we could bring her closure.

252
00:13:03.149 --> 00:13:05.050
A twin. Huh.

253
00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:08.251
That is a real bond.
(INHALES SHARPLY)

254
00:13:09.289 --> 00:13:13.351
I would like to help.
but this is a long shot.

255
00:13:14.027 --> 00:13:17.429
but I kept thinking about
those autopsy photos.

256
00:13:17.563 --> 00:13:20.089
The medical
training. the red hair.

257
00:13:20.199 --> 00:13:23.567
and suddenly I was
reminded of this incident

258
00:13:23.670 --> 00:13:26.139
that happened back when I
was becoming a senior resident.

259
00:13:26.239 --> 00:13:27.571
That was what. in 2002?

260
00:13:27.674 --> 00:13:30.109
Yeah. About then.

261
00:13:30.209 --> 00:13:33.475
I got a call from an
attending. he needed stitches.

262
00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:35.706
He called you? Why
not go to the hospital?

263
00:13:35.848 --> 00:13:37.407
Because he was embarrassed.

264
00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:40.947
When I got to the
townhouse. I found out why.

265
00:13:41.788 --> 00:13:44.815
He had bruising and cuts

266
00:13:44.924 --> 00:13:47.917
and what appeared
to be human bite marks

267
00:13:48.027 --> 00:13:49.859
on his inner thigh and scrotum.

268
00:13:49.962 --> 00:13:52.625
He claimed it happened during
some sex game gone awry.

269
00:13:52.732 --> 00:13:53.995
But you didn't believe him? No.

270
00:13:54.434 --> 00:13:57.768
I asked him if his partner
needed medical attention.

271
00:13:58.938 --> 00:14:02.875
He assured me that she
was fine. and that she had left.

272
00:14:03.443 --> 00:14:07.574
Whoever she was. I could sense
that she was still in the house.

273
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:11.708
There was that clump of
red hair on the floorboards

274
00:14:11.818 --> 00:14:14.947
and I... I could smell her.

275
00:14:15.088 --> 00:14:16.181
Okay. Doc.

276
00:14:16.289 --> 00:14:18.622
No. really. I could.

277
00:14:18.725 --> 00:14:20.660
And it wasn't the sex and
it wasn't the hormones.

278
00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:21.784
it was her fear.

279
00:14:22.362 --> 00:14:25.764
It has a very real
scent. like. uh. ammonia.

280
00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:27.766
What was the name
of the attending?

281
00:14:27.900 --> 00:14:28.900
(CHUCKLES)

282
00:14:29.936 --> 00:14:31.928
I don't wanna
incriminate anybody.

283
00:14:32.038 --> 00:14:34.132
I... I could be wrong.

284
00:14:34.607 --> 00:14:35.631
(SCOFFS)

285
00:14:35.742 --> 00:14:38.541
But I remember
the street. though.

286
00:14:39.379 --> 00:14:41.610
Convent Avenue in Harlem.

287
00:14:46.719 --> 00:14:49.211
The townhouse has
a lovely Juliet balcony.

288
00:14:57.764 --> 00:14:59.232
Sarge. Fin.

289
00:14:59.465 --> 00:15:02.128
Wasn't expecting you.
These are the Changs.

290
00:15:02.268 --> 00:15:04.760
They bought the house four
years ago. did a renovation.

291
00:15:04.871 --> 00:15:06.601
Before that. it had
fallen into disrepair

292
00:15:06.706 --> 00:15:08.732
after the 2007 death
of Manon Favreau.

293
00:15:08.841 --> 00:15:10.400
She was a widow
whose husband's family

294
00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.030
actually built this
house in the 1880s.

295
00:15:12.078 --> 00:15:14.656
Okay. thanks for the history lesson.
Carisi. Who lived here in 2002?

296
00:15:14.680 --> 00:15:15.991
Well. we're looking
at tax records.

297
00:15:16.015 --> 00:15:17.449
utility bills. but.
realistically...

298
00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:19.314
Yates could just be
pulling Rollins' chain.

299
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.082
I don't see what he gets
out of that. So we're here.

300
00:15:22.755 --> 00:15:24.900
The couple's given us permission
to do a non-invasive search?

301
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:25.924
But after all this time.

302
00:15:26.025 --> 00:15:27.436
what are the chances
we're gonna find something?

303
00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:30.828
Sergeant. you're here.
Come look at what we found.

304
00:15:34.667 --> 00:15:37.364
The CSU techs picked up
an image using the GPR.

305
00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:38.597
FIN: What's that?

306
00:15:38.704 --> 00:15:40.195
Ground Penetrating Radar.

307
00:15:40.540 --> 00:15:42.668
It's like a sonogram that
can see inside that wall?

308
00:15:42.775 --> 00:15:45.438
Yes. Fin. See. it
used to be a chimney.

309
00:15:45.878 --> 00:15:48.712
Okay. what's that shadow?
There's something in there.

310
00:15:50.116 --> 00:15:52.017
I bet that's another
Yates victim.

311
00:15:52.118 --> 00:15:53.643
So what. we rip down the wall?

312
00:15:53.886 --> 00:15:58.256
Okay. go tell the owners that that
non-invasive search just became invasive.

313
00:15:58.658 --> 00:15:59.658
(SIGHS)

314
00:16:00.426 --> 00:16:02.156
(WHIRRING)

315
00:16:05.832 --> 00:16:07.164
Little help here.

316
00:16:18.344 --> 00:16:19.642
It's a suitcase.

317
00:16:20.746 --> 00:16:22.408
Great. let's get it out.

318
00:16:26.018 --> 00:16:28.783
(GRUNTS) Something
inside. Should we open it?

319
00:16:28.888 --> 00:16:30.151
Yeah. Go ahead.

320
00:16:35.461 --> 00:16:36.461
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

321
00:16:40.700 --> 00:16:42.168
She's mummified.

322
00:16:48.741 --> 00:16:51.939
So Yates' tip paid off. there was
a body in the Harlem townhouse?

323
00:16:52.044 --> 00:16:53.603
In the wall. mummified.

324
00:16:54.413 --> 00:16:55.881
Anything else in the house?

325
00:16:56.415 --> 00:16:58.816
Fin and Carisi are
searching the place with CSU.

326
00:16:58.918 --> 00:17:00.181
We're getting a DNA sample.

327
00:17:00.286 --> 00:17:01.879
As soon as the ME
dates the decomp.

328
00:17:01.988 --> 00:17:03.148
we'll search missing persons.

329
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.213
Why not just ask Yates?

330
00:17:04.323 --> 00:17:05.791
He's a convicted serial killer

331
00:17:05.892 --> 00:17:07.469
who tipped you off to
the location of a corpse

332
00:17:07.493 --> 00:17:09.086
in a house where
he also puts himself.

333
00:17:09.195 --> 00:17:12.165
Rollins has been working him.
He swears that it wasn't him.

334
00:17:12.265 --> 00:17:13.785
(CHUCKLES) You've
got to be kidding me.

335
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:17.640
RUDNICK: The incisions seem to have
been made by a medical professional.

336
00:17:17.670 --> 00:17:21.129
Pubis and ilium scraped where they
were separated from the adductors.

337
00:17:21.240 --> 00:17:24.506
So she was dissected just
like Rachel Groves was?

338
00:17:24.610 --> 00:17:26.545
The muscle was cut
away from the bone.

339
00:17:26.646 --> 00:17:28.046
(CLEARS THROAT) Hmm.

340
00:17:28.147 --> 00:17:29.291
Detective. you
look a little peaked.

341
00:17:29.315 --> 00:17:30.315
I'm fine. No. I'm good.

342
00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:32.579
Would you...
Dr. Rudnick. Rollins.

343
00:17:33.252 --> 00:17:36.245
A sergeant and an ADA at an
autopsy? Should I be nervous?

344
00:17:36.355 --> 00:17:37.687
Can you tell us anything?

345
00:17:37.857 --> 00:17:40.224
An autopsy like this
is an enigmatic puzzle.

346
00:17:40.493 --> 00:17:42.724
The body was cut.
broken. and tied

347
00:17:42.828 --> 00:17:44.990
with an electrical cord
to fit in the suitcase.

348
00:17:45.765 --> 00:17:49.293
It had to be uncurled.
X-rayed. rehydrated.

349
00:17:49.402 --> 00:17:51.871
Start at the beginning.
Age. cause of death?

350
00:17:52.338 --> 00:17:57.140
Well. she was a white female. From
her teeth. I'd guess about 25. 5'6".

351
00:17:57.243 --> 00:17:58.267
In good physical health.

352
00:17:58.377 --> 00:17:59.377
Cause of death?

353
00:17:59.478 --> 00:18:03.506
The skull was fractured. but I
believe the cause was strangulation.

354
00:18:03.683 --> 00:18:05.743
The hyoid was also fractured.

355
00:18:06.018 --> 00:18:07.418
Body was wrapped in a blanket.

356
00:18:07.520 --> 00:18:09.148
The dry heat and smoke

357
00:18:09.255 --> 00:18:11.815
from the common chimney
effectively mummified the remains.

358
00:18:12.458 --> 00:18:15.792
And. she was in situ for
over a decade. most likely.

359
00:18:15.895 --> 00:18:17.363
How is it she was discovered?

360
00:18:17.463 --> 00:18:20.399
Actually. it was a tip
from Yates. Dr. Yates?

361
00:18:20.499 --> 00:18:21.933
It's a tip or a confession?

362
00:18:22.034 --> 00:18:23.297
Is this another one of his?

363
00:18:23.402 --> 00:18:25.428
I noted no nail polish.

364
00:18:25.538 --> 00:18:28.167
But the incisions do show
evidence of medical technique.

365
00:18:28.274 --> 00:18:31.802
And the fractured skull is not
inconsistent with Yates' MO.

366
00:18:31.911 --> 00:18:34.881
But strangulation is. And
the victim was a redhead.

367
00:18:34.981 --> 00:18:37.314
Yes. So was Rachel Groves.

368
00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:39.210
I'll need to do a
thorough examination.

369
00:18:39.819 --> 00:18:42.550
So far. I've found no
trace of the killer's DNA.

370
00:18:42.655 --> 00:18:45.955
Which is also not
inconsistent with Yates' MO.

371
00:18:48.227 --> 00:18:50.389
"Also not inconsistent
with Yates' MO."

372
00:18:50.496 --> 00:18:52.474
That's ME talk for. "Yates
did it. but don't quote me."

373
00:18:52.498 --> 00:18:53.830
Yates is appealing
his conviction.

374
00:18:53.933 --> 00:18:55.243
Why would he tip us
off to another victim?

375
00:18:55.267 --> 00:18:56.963
He's sick. but he's not stupid.

376
00:18:57.069 --> 00:18:58.149
Rollins. all due respect...

377
00:18:58.237 --> 00:18:59.514
Don't start a sentence that way.

378
00:18:59.538 --> 00:19:01.166
Fine. If Yates didn't do it.

379
00:19:01.273 --> 00:19:02.873
then how did he know
that body was there?

380
00:19:04.076 --> 00:19:05.076
(SCOFFS)

381
00:19:13.919 --> 00:19:16.320
Your DA thinks I'm
the one who did this?

382
00:19:16.422 --> 00:19:19.358
You know. I am the one
who told you all about her.

383
00:19:19.592 --> 00:19:21.891
That's exactly why
he thinks you did it.

384
00:19:23.329 --> 00:19:26.128
Is he always so
circular in his reasoning?

385
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:28.410
You told me that you
were called to that house.

386
00:19:28.434 --> 00:19:29.993
that you knew a woman was there.

387
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:32.604
Do you know who she was?

388
00:19:32.872 --> 00:19:35.899
I do. I even know
who killed her.

389
00:19:37.343 --> 00:19:42.338
But enough talk about
what I can do for you.

390
00:19:43.616 --> 00:19:45.482
Let's talk about how
you can help me.

391
00:19:46.919 --> 00:19:50.185
Yates wants to touch
his fiancée. Susie Frain?

392
00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:52.757
Hasn't he touched
enough women already?

393
00:19:52.858 --> 00:19:55.418
Look. they've been together for
20 years. He's never hurt Susie.

394
00:19:55.528 --> 00:19:57.258
And she's okay
with conjugal visits?

395
00:19:57.363 --> 00:19:58.592
She called about it twice.

396
00:19:58.698 --> 00:19:59.825
Every pot has a lid.

397
00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:03.025
Lovely. You do realize how this
would look if word got out. right?

398
00:20:03.436 --> 00:20:06.270
Yates is already on the hook
for multiple rapes and murder.

399
00:20:06.472 --> 00:20:09.931
now he wants to trade
crime tips for conjugal visits.

400
00:20:10.042 --> 00:20:12.842
If Yates is telling the truth. there
could be another serial out there.

401
00:20:12.945 --> 00:20:14.277
So pick your poison. Counselor.

402
00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:18.249
Fine. Bring the fiancée
upstate. Let them conjugate.

403
00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.995
And then interrogate
both of them afterwards.

404
00:20:20.019 --> 00:20:21.579
You better be right
about this. Rollins.

405
00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:31.255
(SUSIE AND YATES MOANING)

406
00:20:32.398 --> 00:20:33.661
Okay. we good?

407
00:20:40.339 --> 00:20:42.035
Time's up. Coming in!

408
00:20:50.182 --> 00:20:53.482
Ms. Frain. before you leave. uh. my
detectives have some questions for you.

409
00:20:54.386 --> 00:20:55.752
No one told me about this.

410
00:20:55.921 --> 00:20:57.549
Oh. hey. it's all right.

411
00:20:59.158 --> 00:21:00.490
Just tell the truth.

412
00:21:03.329 --> 00:21:05.169
All right. we have some
questions for you. too.

413
00:21:05.264 --> 00:21:06.789
So much for afterglow.

414
00:21:07.299 --> 00:21:09.598
But a deal is a deal.

415
00:21:10.202 --> 00:21:12.603
Come in here. We'll
have more privacy.

416
00:21:14.807 --> 00:21:16.551
I hope. now that you've
found these two bodies.

417
00:21:16.575 --> 00:21:18.407
you'll be releasing Greg
as soon as possible.

418
00:21:18.511 --> 00:21:19.570
Come again?

419
00:21:19.712 --> 00:21:21.977
I always knew Greg wasn't
capable of these crimes.

420
00:21:22.248 --> 00:21:23.546
He was framed.

421
00:21:23.983 --> 00:21:25.246
The poor girl in Pelham Bay.

422
00:21:25.351 --> 00:21:27.286
she must have been
murdered after he was arrested

423
00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:29.651
or you would have found the
body when you first searched.

424
00:21:29.755 --> 00:21:31.348
Oh. did Greg tell you that?

425
00:21:31.490 --> 00:21:36.622
It's common sense. And Lena. we
were all friends. Greg was fond of her.

426
00:21:37.096 --> 00:21:38.792
Hold... Hold up. Who's Lena?

427
00:21:39.165 --> 00:21:41.896
Lena Grunwald.
The girl in the wall.

428
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:46.102
I thought she'd gone home to
Switzerland. But she must have never left.

429
00:21:47.406 --> 00:21:48.840
Lena was a lovely girl.

430
00:21:48.941 --> 00:21:50.910
She was over from
Switzerland for her doctorate.

431
00:21:51.010 --> 00:21:52.535
and they met at Columbia.

432
00:21:52.645 --> 00:21:53.840
Met who?

433
00:21:54.213 --> 00:21:55.442
Her fiancé.

434
00:21:56.348 --> 00:21:59.682
(CLEARS THROAT) Well.
on the night that I stitched him.

435
00:21:59.785 --> 00:22:02.118
he said that it was a
sex game gone wrong.

436
00:22:02.221 --> 00:22:05.817
but he had to have
tortured... (GASPS) Oh...

437
00:22:05.925 --> 00:22:09.089
He might have sealed her in
that wall while she was still alive.

438
00:22:09.195 --> 00:22:10.788
Stay with us. Dr. Yates.

439
00:22:11.230 --> 00:22:13.722
Oh. yes. I'm sorry.
That poor woman.

440
00:22:13.833 --> 00:22:15.358
You were gonna give us a name.

441
00:22:16.101 --> 00:22:17.831
I was. Apologies.

442
00:22:17.937 --> 00:22:19.200
Uh. Carl.

443
00:22:19.305 --> 00:22:23.174
Yes. When I was a senior
resident. he was an attending.

444
00:22:23.275 --> 00:22:27.406
Strange man. A
little delicate. pale.

445
00:22:27.546 --> 00:22:30.311
He kept to himself. which is
why we were so sort of surprised

446
00:22:30.416 --> 00:22:32.214
when he got engaged to Lena.

447
00:22:32.418 --> 00:22:34.444
Does this delicate
man have a last name?

448
00:22:34.653 --> 00:22:37.418
Rudnick. Uh. Dr. Carl Rudnick.

449
00:22:37.723 --> 00:22:40.249
That's it. we're
done. Rollins...

450
00:22:41.961 --> 00:22:43.657
I went out on a limb for you.

451
00:22:43.762 --> 00:22:44.957
You think this is a game?

452
00:22:45.064 --> 00:22:48.034
You are gonna be transferred so
far upstate your ass is gonna freeze.

453
00:22:48.133 --> 00:22:49.411
Rollins. let's go.
What did I say?

454
00:22:49.435 --> 00:22:50.926
Dr. Carl Rudnick.

455
00:22:51.270 --> 00:22:55.037
Deputy Chief Medical Examiner
in the borough of Manhattan.

456
00:22:55.140 --> 00:22:56.301
He's a serial killer?

457
00:22:56.408 --> 00:22:58.809
Wait. Carl became an ME?

458
00:22:58.911 --> 00:23:02.780
Oh. no. that... That
really is... That is perfect.

459
00:23:02.882 --> 00:23:05.875
He never liked people.
but he always liked cutting.

460
00:23:05.985 --> 00:23:07.112
Don't even try. Yates.

461
00:23:07.219 --> 00:23:09.779
No. stay. Please.
I need to know.

462
00:23:09.889 --> 00:23:12.381
did he do any of the autopsies
on the girls you found?

463
00:23:13.125 --> 00:23:14.718
Nadia. maybe?

464
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:16.688
Come on. a man like that.

465
00:23:16.795 --> 00:23:19.115
with all those female bodies
being delivered to the morgue.

466
00:23:19.265 --> 00:23:21.860
having been tortured to death...

467
00:23:23.402 --> 00:23:24.768
That is a trigger.

468
00:23:25.337 --> 00:23:26.635
He would get off on them

469
00:23:26.739 --> 00:23:29.903
and then he would want to
go do another one for himself.

470
00:23:30.009 --> 00:23:32.478
That girl. The girl
in Pelham Bay...

471
00:23:34.847 --> 00:23:37.646
Did Rudnick do her autopsy. too?

472
00:23:40.619 --> 00:23:42.850
Have another ME
recheck the body.

473
00:23:43.289 --> 00:23:44.814
His report didn't say so.

474
00:23:44.924 --> 00:23:46.358
but I'll bet you
dollars to donuts

475
00:23:46.458 --> 00:23:49.257
he cut that girl up
while she was still alive.

476
00:24:02.441 --> 00:24:04.672
Accusing the deputy chief
ME of rape and murder?

477
00:24:04.910 --> 00:24:07.789
And they offered this conspiracy
theory right after their conjugal visit?

478
00:24:07.813 --> 00:24:09.179
Yeah. I know. He worked you two.

479
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:13.377
And the fiancée worked us. Give
Yates points. That's a bold move.

480
00:24:13.485 --> 00:24:15.647
I'm sorry. You all
were right. I was wrong.

481
00:24:15.888 --> 00:24:19.120
Hold on. Rollins. Now.
look. I'm still only mid-search.

482
00:24:19.224 --> 00:24:21.090
but there was a Lena
Grunwald from Switzerland

483
00:24:21.193 --> 00:24:22.525
who went to
Columbia at that time.

484
00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:24.529
Now. as far as I can
tell. she never graduates.

485
00:24:24.630 --> 00:24:27.464
She just disappears off
the grid in the winter of 2002.

486
00:24:27.866 --> 00:24:29.266
You actually looked into this?

487
00:24:29.535 --> 00:24:30.628
Yeah. Counselor. I did.

488
00:24:30.736 --> 00:24:34.036
'Cause if Yates is taking a flyer for an
appeal. then we have to rule this out.

489
00:24:35.641 --> 00:24:39.772
Now. I'm still new here. But how
well do you guys know Carl Rudnick?

490
00:24:40.145 --> 00:24:41.773
He got here right
before you did.

491
00:24:41.880 --> 00:24:43.405
He came out of
Miami-Dade. I think.

492
00:24:43.882 --> 00:24:47.842
Carisi's right. Yates is looking
to overturn his conviction.

493
00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:50.960
Did Rudnick ever mention that he
went to medical school with Yates?

494
00:24:51.056 --> 00:24:52.422
No. he didn't.

495
00:24:52.524 --> 00:24:55.460
So what if he did?
Yates kidnapped. raped.

496
00:24:55.561 --> 00:24:57.553
tortured. and murdered Nadia.

497
00:24:58.130 --> 00:24:59.154
He is guilty.

498
00:24:59.298 --> 00:25:02.268
The only reason he's bringing up
conflicting evidence is for his appeal.

499
00:25:02.368 --> 00:25:03.678
Still. if they did
know each other.

500
00:25:03.702 --> 00:25:05.113
then Rudnick should
have recused himself.

501
00:25:05.137 --> 00:25:06.337
That's easy enough to confirm.

502
00:25:06.438 --> 00:25:08.450
And while you're at it. see if
Rudnick has any connection to

503
00:25:08.474 --> 00:25:09.533
the townhouse in Harlem.

504
00:25:09.842 --> 00:25:12.607
or if he even knew this
supposed fiancée. Lena Grunwald.

505
00:25:16.749 --> 00:25:19.685
SUSIE: That's Lena.
With Carl. me. and Greg.

506
00:25:20.652 --> 00:25:22.746
New Year's Eve.
2001. in Montreal.

507
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:24.199
BENSON: So you knew
each other well enough

508
00:25:24.223 --> 00:25:25.533
that you'd all go on
vacation together?

509
00:25:25.557 --> 00:25:27.924
Oh. yeah. Canada.
Europe a few times.

510
00:25:28.594 --> 00:25:30.062
Lena spoke French and German.

511
00:25:30.162 --> 00:25:32.688
She was a great tour
guide. A lovely person.

512
00:25:33.032 --> 00:25:35.524
What can you tell us about her
relationship with Carl Rudnick?

513
00:25:35.934 --> 00:25:37.402
Tempestuous.

514
00:25:37.569 --> 00:25:40.266
They fought. especially when
they drank. And they both drank.

515
00:25:40.372 --> 00:25:42.466
She loved her Gewürztraminer.

516
00:25:42.741 --> 00:25:44.437
Remember the last
time you saw her?

517
00:25:45.010 --> 00:25:46.672
I remember when she left.

518
00:25:47.813 --> 00:25:50.305
Greg threw me a birthday party.
and Carl brought a new date.

519
00:25:50.749 --> 00:25:52.513
He said Lena had broken
off their engagement

520
00:25:52.618 --> 00:25:53.728
and moved back to Switzerland.

521
00:25:53.752 --> 00:25:55.050
And that was...

522
00:25:55.354 --> 00:25:57.220
Early February. 2002.

523
00:25:57.356 --> 00:25:59.222
So you didn't
think it was strange

524
00:25:59.324 --> 00:26:01.122
that she didn't say
goodbye to you herself?

525
00:26:01.493 --> 00:26:02.620
I did. actually.

526
00:26:02.728 --> 00:26:04.663
In Montreal. they were
going at each other.

527
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:06.858
On the flight back.
Lena told me that

528
00:26:06.965 --> 00:26:09.366
if anything ever
happened to her. Carl did it.

529
00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:12.837
Why didn't you call the police?

530
00:26:13.105 --> 00:26:14.105
I was going to.

531
00:26:14.173 --> 00:26:16.005
But then I got a note
from Lena with a photo

532
00:26:16.108 --> 00:26:17.872
of herself in her
village. Grindelwald.

533
00:26:18.610 --> 00:26:20.841
She apologized. She said
she just had to get away.

534
00:26:20.946 --> 00:26:22.539
And you're sure that it was her?

535
00:26:22.981 --> 00:26:24.279
I thought it was.

536
00:26:24.383 --> 00:26:26.284
You think you may have
kept that note and photo?

537
00:26:26.385 --> 00:26:29.253
I have tons of boxes
in mini-storage.

538
00:26:29.354 --> 00:26:31.255
You think it will
help if I find it?

539
00:26:33.492 --> 00:26:36.485
BENSON: Okay. so Rudnick and
Yates overlapped in medical school.

540
00:26:36.595 --> 00:26:38.996
and Lena was in business
school at the same time.

541
00:26:39.131 --> 00:26:41.464
And Susie just told us
that they were all friends.

542
00:26:41.600 --> 00:26:44.832
Which. as Carisi said.
Rudnick should have disclosed.

543
00:26:44.937 --> 00:26:46.748
It still doesn't mean that
Rudnick is good for this.

544
00:26:46.772 --> 00:26:50.903
Remember. Rollins. Yates tried to
pin Nadia's death on Will Halstead.

545
00:26:51.009 --> 00:26:52.033
He's an opportunist.

546
00:26:52.144 --> 00:26:54.909
I know he is. And I know he's
good for Nadia's murder and.

547
00:26:55.013 --> 00:26:56.276
what. a dozen before.

548
00:26:56.648 --> 00:27:00.085
But this woman in the
wall. I'm not sure about.

549
00:27:00.185 --> 00:27:01.983
'Cause. look. I did a search.

550
00:27:02.087 --> 00:27:06.286
I was trying to find who exactly
lived in this house in 2002.

551
00:27:06.558 --> 00:27:11.587
Now Con Ed and phone bills
both went to Manon Favreau.

552
00:27:11.697 --> 00:27:15.634
The name on the cable
bill. it's under Carl Rudnick.

553
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:20.030
While it was owned by Manon
Favreau? So he was renting?

554
00:27:20.139 --> 00:27:21.471
More like house-sitting.

555
00:27:21.573 --> 00:27:25.669
It turns out her maiden
name was "Manon Rudnick".

556
00:27:25.777 --> 00:27:27.075
She's Carl Rudnick's great-aunt.

557
00:27:27.179 --> 00:27:28.511
I mean. these ancestry websites.

558
00:27:28.614 --> 00:27:29.958
you'd be surprised what
they know about you.

559
00:27:29.982 --> 00:27:32.247
Okay. So Rudnick
neglected to mention

560
00:27:32.351 --> 00:27:35.378
that the body that we found
was in his aunt's house.

561
00:27:35.487 --> 00:27:37.768
and he was living there when
it was plastered in the wall.

562
00:27:37.823 --> 00:27:40.884
Damn. He autopsied
his own fiancée?

563
00:27:40.993 --> 00:27:43.428
Thirteen years
after he killed her.

564
00:27:43.529 --> 00:27:46.328
We don't know that yet. We don't
even know if the body is Lena's.

565
00:27:46.431 --> 00:27:48.332
Susie told us that Lena sent her

566
00:27:48.433 --> 00:27:50.265
a picture of herself
from Switzerland.

567
00:27:50.402 --> 00:27:53.122
Yeah. well. if she did send that
photo. that's the last trace of her.

568
00:27:53.405 --> 00:27:55.465
BENSON: Do we have any
proof that the body was hers?

569
00:27:55.574 --> 00:27:57.270
DNA. dental records. anything?

570
00:27:57.376 --> 00:27:58.674
FIN: I called Warner.

571
00:27:58.844 --> 00:28:01.905
She said. according to
Rudnick. there's no way to ID her.

572
00:28:02.047 --> 00:28:03.208
There's a shock.

573
00:28:03.315 --> 00:28:05.807
Okay. I'll call the
chief medical examiner

574
00:28:05.918 --> 00:28:07.910
and see if he'll
authorize Warner

575
00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:09.955
to independently
redo both autopsies.

576
00:28:10.522 --> 00:28:12.457
preferably when
Rudnick's not there.

577
00:28:15.661 --> 00:28:17.661
RUDNICK: (OVER SPEAKERS)
<i>The body's well-preserved.</i>

578
00:28:17.729 --> 00:28:20.289
<i>most likely from the
frigid water temperatures.</i>

579
00:28:20.399 --> 00:28:21.890
<i>which lasted well into April.</i>

580
00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:23.024
Let's stop here.

581
00:28:23.335 --> 00:28:25.736
Dr. Rudnick's time of
death may be mistaken.

582
00:28:25.837 --> 00:28:26.998
"May be"?

583
00:28:27.105 --> 00:28:28.198
He says early April.

584
00:28:28.307 --> 00:28:29.969
but based on the
crime scene photos.

585
00:28:30.075 --> 00:28:32.943
it appears the body wasn't
wrapped in plastic or a tarp.

586
00:28:33.045 --> 00:28:34.240
But that's in his report.

587
00:28:34.413 --> 00:28:37.815
Yes. but if this body went
into the water in mid-April.

588
00:28:37.950 --> 00:28:41.318
the fish or crabs would have
nibbled away at the soft tissue.

589
00:28:41.453 --> 00:28:43.012
So. it's more likely early May?

590
00:28:43.121 --> 00:28:44.214
WARNER: I think so.

591
00:28:44.556 --> 00:28:45.990
I'm surprised. frankly.

592
00:28:46.758 --> 00:28:50.251
I mean. it's careless. and
Dr. Rudnick is meticulous to a fault.

593
00:28:50.362 --> 00:28:52.024
He's one of the top
MEs in the country.

594
00:28:52.197 --> 00:28:53.474
What else do you know about him?

595
00:28:53.498 --> 00:28:56.832
He's a guy who works six days a
week. never puts in for overtime.

596
00:28:57.069 --> 00:28:58.594
We all figure family money.

597
00:28:59.238 --> 00:29:00.900
He's obsessed with
his work. Okay. okay.

598
00:29:01.907 --> 00:29:03.102
So his timeline is off.

599
00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:07.076
Is it possible that
he's overworked?

600
00:29:07.246 --> 00:29:09.875
Maybe. And here's
another omission I noticed.

601
00:29:10.482 --> 00:29:12.041
His report neglects to mention

602
00:29:12.150 --> 00:29:14.210
that the dismemberment
took place ante mortem.

603
00:29:18.857 --> 00:29:20.485
So Rachel Groves
was alive? You sure?

604
00:29:20.592 --> 00:29:21.651
Positive.

605
00:29:22.227 --> 00:29:25.857
Cutting into live tissue
always causes a vital reaction.

606
00:29:25.964 --> 00:29:28.456
markedly different from
cutting into dead tissue.

607
00:29:28.567 --> 00:29:32.561
And there's no way an ME would
leave this out or possibly mistake the two?

608
00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:35.832
No. Now you wanna
tell me what this is about?

609
00:29:36.475 --> 00:29:37.475
(SCOFFS)

610
00:29:38.143 --> 00:29:42.638
Uh. I'm sorry Melinda. I can't.
This is an active investigation.

611
00:29:47.519 --> 00:29:49.988
Before I re-autopsy
this mummified body.

612
00:29:50.088 --> 00:29:51.368
is there anything I should know?

613
00:29:51.456 --> 00:29:54.620
Uh. well. she may
be a Swiss national.

614
00:29:54.726 --> 00:29:56.160
We haven't been able to ID her.

615
00:29:56.461 --> 00:29:57.622
That may be helpful.

616
00:29:57.729 --> 00:29:58.788
Okay.

617
00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:04.527
Melinda. watch your
back with Rudnick.

618
00:30:12.444 --> 00:30:13.912
What am I looking at here?

619
00:30:14.012 --> 00:30:16.914
It's proof that the body in
that wall was Lena Grunwald.

620
00:30:17.049 --> 00:30:19.518
Okay. Warner found these
gold overlays on her teeth

621
00:30:19.618 --> 00:30:22.417
that are specific to
German-Swiss dentists.

622
00:30:22.521 --> 00:30:25.218
Yeah. another detail Dr. Rudnick
did not put in his autopsy report.

623
00:30:25.324 --> 00:30:28.556
We confirmed with her dentist
in Switzerland. It is Lena's body.

624
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:30.090
She never went home?

625
00:30:30.195 --> 00:30:31.515
Well. here's
where it gets tricky.

626
00:30:31.563 --> 00:30:33.225
I finally heard back
from my guy at TSA.

627
00:30:33.332 --> 00:30:36.427
Now according to them.
Lena Grunwald left JFK

628
00:30:36.535 --> 00:30:38.834
for Zurich on
February 11th. 2002.

629
00:30:39.404 --> 00:30:41.339
So? We can't pinpoint
her time of death.

630
00:30:42.007 --> 00:30:44.018
She must have come back.
been murdered sometime later.

631
00:30:44.042 --> 00:30:46.238
Yeah. but there's no
record of her coming back.

632
00:30:46.578 --> 00:30:48.410
So. on a hunch. I
looked at Rudnick's travel.

633
00:30:48.513 --> 00:30:50.675
Now this guy. he's got the
opposite problem. all right?

634
00:30:50.782 --> 00:30:53.479
He returned from Paris
to JFK on February 15th.

635
00:30:53.585 --> 00:30:56.214
but there's no record of him
leaving the US. or even Canada.

636
00:30:56.321 --> 00:30:58.266
Okay. You got a theory
to go with this travel log?

637
00:30:58.290 --> 00:31:01.454
What if Rudnick left the
US using Lena's passport

638
00:31:01.560 --> 00:31:03.119
and then came back as himself?

639
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:09.327
You're suggesting he was able
to pass as a woman. post 9/11?

640
00:31:09.434 --> 00:31:12.598
Yeah. a red-haired lady
with a Swiss passport.

641
00:31:12.871 --> 00:31:15.340
So outside their profile.
nobody took a second look at her.

642
00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:17.102
And Rachel. the
victim from the bay.

643
00:31:17.275 --> 00:31:20.245
I mean. she was last seen
leaving her shelter with a woman.

644
00:31:20.345 --> 00:31:21.574
Or someone dressed like one.

645
00:31:21.947 --> 00:31:23.427
You using facial
recognition software?

646
00:31:23.515 --> 00:31:26.508
We are. Liv is headed to 1PP now

647
00:31:26.618 --> 00:31:28.849
to get the okay to bring
Rudnick in for questioning.

648
00:31:29.588 --> 00:31:32.114
Call her off. We'll
ask forgiveness later.

649
00:31:33.024 --> 00:31:35.224
For now. I'll find a pretext
to invite him to my office.

650
00:31:35.293 --> 00:31:37.305
So while he's with you. how
about a warrant for his house?

651
00:31:37.329 --> 00:31:39.329
I mean. knives. dresses.
who knows what we'll find.

652
00:31:39.398 --> 00:31:40.696
All right.

653
00:31:42.567 --> 00:31:43.567
(SIGHS)

654
00:31:44.403 --> 00:31:45.427
Please come in.

655
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:48.182
Dr. Rudnick. just so you know.
everything in this room is recorded.

656
00:31:48.206 --> 00:31:49.799
Have a seat.

657
00:31:49.908 --> 00:31:52.503
Um. Yates is
appealing his conviction.

658
00:31:52.611 --> 00:31:55.274
So this conversation may be
discoverable as part of that process.

659
00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:57.042
Of course. I also
record everything.

660
00:31:58.583 --> 00:31:59.983
Oh. Sergeant Benson.

661
00:32:00.318 --> 00:32:02.446
Yes. Dr. Rudnick. thank
you so much for meeting us.

662
00:32:03.422 --> 00:32:04.981
Just have a few
questions for you.

663
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.285
Certainly.

664
00:32:08.827 --> 00:32:12.264
Okay. this file. do
you recognize it?

665
00:32:13.832 --> 00:32:17.132
Yes. This is the autopsy report

666
00:32:17.235 --> 00:32:19.204
of the Jane Doe you
found mummified.

667
00:32:19.304 --> 00:32:20.499
The Yates victim.

668
00:32:20.605 --> 00:32:23.905
BENSON: And the address where the
body was found. do you recognize that?

669
00:32:24.009 --> 00:32:26.376
RUDNICK: That's bizarre.
I never noticed the address.

670
00:32:28.113 --> 00:32:31.015
My eyes were on
the poor girl's remains.

671
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:33.308
So you do recognize the address?

672
00:32:33.418 --> 00:32:34.886
It was my great aunt's house.

673
00:32:35.320 --> 00:32:36.447
FIN: Look at this.

674
00:32:38.356 --> 00:32:40.587
Keeps autopsy photos bedside.

675
00:32:40.692 --> 00:32:42.772
He'll probably claim he
takes his work home with him.

676
00:32:43.161 --> 00:32:45.357
BENSON: And this
woman. you recognize her?

677
00:32:45.564 --> 00:32:47.897
RUDNICK: Well. yes. of
course. That's Lena Grunwald.

678
00:32:47.999 --> 00:32:50.491
An old flame of mine
from 15 years ago.

679
00:32:51.503 --> 00:32:53.028
I'm sorry. what's
this all about?

680
00:32:53.605 --> 00:32:55.631
We believe the
body found in the wall

681
00:32:55.740 --> 00:32:57.834
of your aunt's house
was Lena Grunwald's.

682
00:33:02.948 --> 00:33:06.646
Oh. my God. I
didn't recognize her.

683
00:33:07.853 --> 00:33:09.287
And how could I. in that state?

684
00:33:09.387 --> 00:33:11.379
Are you suggesting
I autopsied my ex?

685
00:33:11.556 --> 00:33:13.252
So you didn't know
that she was dead?

686
00:33:13.358 --> 00:33:15.678
Well. of course not. Last
time I saw her was at the airport

687
00:33:15.760 --> 00:33:17.126
when she left for Switzerland.

688
00:33:18.129 --> 00:33:19.707
She must have come
back without my knowledge

689
00:33:19.731 --> 00:33:21.165
and fallen back in with Yates.

690
00:33:22.367 --> 00:33:25.496
Who took her to
your aunt's house.

691
00:33:25.604 --> 00:33:28.665
killed her. and
entombed her in the wall?

692
00:33:28.840 --> 00:33:30.706
That's an incredible
coincidence.

693
00:33:30.809 --> 00:33:33.438
Not really. We all
knew each other.

694
00:33:33.545 --> 00:33:35.411
And I occasionally
entertained at that home.

695
00:33:35.647 --> 00:33:37.172
So. you and Yates
knew each other?

696
00:33:37.949 --> 00:33:40.043
Yes. of course. It's
public knowledge.

697
00:33:40.519 --> 00:33:43.455
We were in med school at the
same time. a few years apart.

698
00:33:44.322 --> 00:33:45.950
He was always
rather jealous of me.

699
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:48.583
RAFAEL: <i>You and
Yates were colleagues.</i>

700
00:33:48.693 --> 00:33:50.453
<i>Did you ever think to
mention that to anyone?</i>

701
00:33:51.530 --> 00:33:52.691
Well. frankly. no.

702
00:33:53.098 --> 00:33:54.726
When did you last
hear from Lena?

703
00:33:54.833 --> 00:33:57.667
(SIGHS) We broke
up amidst a hard winter.

704
00:33:57.769 --> 00:33:59.635
<i>It was 2002. 2003?</i>

705
00:34:00.071 --> 00:34:01.699
And that son of a bitch.

706
00:34:02.440 --> 00:34:04.671
He always had a thing for Lena.

707
00:34:04.776 --> 00:34:06.972
And killing her is his
way of hurting me.

708
00:34:07.445 --> 00:34:09.038
He did this to hurt you and...

709
00:34:10.115 --> 00:34:12.778
And yet you didn't know
about it for 13 years?

710
00:34:12.951 --> 00:34:14.829
RUDNICK: <i>Well. what other
explanation could there be?</i>

711
00:34:14.853 --> 00:34:16.412
<i>He knew the house. he knew her.</i>

712
00:34:16.521 --> 00:34:19.719
and he's a convicted
serial killer. and ipso facto...

713
00:34:26.898 --> 00:34:28.924
Oh. you can't think I had
anything to do with this.

714
00:34:29.868 --> 00:34:31.131
RAFAEL: <i>We can't?</i>

715
00:34:31.469 --> 00:34:33.301
RUDNICK: <i>Oh.
it's patently absurd.</i>

716
00:34:37.075 --> 00:34:40.341
Dr. Rudnick. then
you wouldn't mind

717
00:34:40.679 --> 00:34:42.614
working through
some of the other.

718
00:34:42.714 --> 00:34:44.580
uh. inconsistencies
that we've found?

719
00:34:44.983 --> 00:34:46.349
Well. not at all.

720
00:34:46.952 --> 00:34:49.547
Given the change in
tenor of this conversation.

721
00:34:49.654 --> 00:34:51.088
I'm contacting my lawyer.

722
00:34:51.189 --> 00:34:53.055
I'd like to exercise that right.

723
00:34:55.093 --> 00:34:56.652
(SIGHS) Feel free.

724
00:34:57.295 --> 00:35:00.163
We will wait to
continue questioning you

725
00:35:00.265 --> 00:35:01.494
until a lawyer arrives.

726
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:17.306
You realize that
if he is guilty.

727
00:35:17.415 --> 00:35:19.384
then every case
he's testified in...

728
00:35:19.484 --> 00:35:21.612
I know. Every autopsy
he's performed...

729
00:35:21.853 --> 00:35:23.531
I don't even wanna think
about how many convictions

730
00:35:23.555 --> 00:35:24.579
will have to be reopened.

731
00:35:24.689 --> 00:35:26.248
(SCOFFS) Olivia.

732
00:35:27.125 --> 00:35:28.325
Rita. What are you doing here?

733
00:35:28.393 --> 00:35:30.794
I was working out a plea deal
when I got a message from Carl.

734
00:35:30.996 --> 00:35:32.828
Carl. You're
representing Dr. Rudnick?

735
00:35:33.365 --> 00:35:36.096
Everyone is entitled to the
best defense they can afford.

736
00:35:36.534 --> 00:35:40.096
And Dr. Rudnick. or his family.
can afford a very good one.

737
00:35:40.205 --> 00:35:42.299
And that. of course.
is all that matters.

738
00:35:42.574 --> 00:35:46.375
My client's waiting. He'll be coming
with me. He is done talking to you.

739
00:35:47.846 --> 00:35:49.109
Actually.

740
00:35:50.849 --> 00:35:52.249
he won't be leaving.

741
00:35:58.256 --> 00:36:01.420
Rita. It's very good of you
to come on such short notice.

742
00:36:01.526 --> 00:36:04.052
Of course. Carl. But I'm
afraid I have some bad news.

743
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:06.529
Carl Rudnick.
you're under arrest

744
00:36:06.631 --> 00:36:09.760
for the murders of Rachel
Groves and Lena Grunwald.

745
00:36:09.868 --> 00:36:11.461
You have the right
to remain silent.

746
00:36:11.569 --> 00:36:14.437
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

747
00:36:14.973 --> 00:36:16.317
You have the right
to an attorney...

748
00:36:16.341 --> 00:36:17.570
We'll see you in court.

749
00:36:21.513 --> 00:36:23.106
Dr. Rudnick. how do you plead?

750
00:36:23.214 --> 00:36:24.614
Not guilty. Your Honor.

751
00:36:24.716 --> 00:36:27.151
He is a respected deputy
chief medical examiner

752
00:36:27.252 --> 00:36:28.412
for the borough of Manhattan.

753
00:36:28.486 --> 00:36:29.681
I'm aware of that. Counselor.

754
00:36:29.788 --> 00:36:31.518
With an impeccable reputation.

755
00:36:31.623 --> 00:36:35.151
We request ROR. as the charges
are. on their face. ridiculous.

756
00:36:35.326 --> 00:36:36.350
Mr. Barba?

757
00:36:36.561 --> 00:36:39.292
Dr. Rudnick has been charged
with two counts of first degree murder.

758
00:36:39.397 --> 00:36:41.696
one in which the
victim was vivisected.

759
00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:45.459
The other was found entombed
in the wall of his family's home.

760
00:36:45.804 --> 00:36:47.204
He's already
tampered with evidence.

761
00:36:47.272 --> 00:36:50.003
His position has allowed
him to cover up the crimes.

762
00:36:50.475 --> 00:36:52.876
Through several family trusts.

763
00:36:52.977 --> 00:36:54.775
he has the means
and the motive to flee.

764
00:36:55.080 --> 00:36:56.776
And we have reason to believe

765
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:58.440
that he has traveled
internationally

766
00:36:58.550 --> 00:37:00.951
using passports from one
of his victims in the past.

767
00:37:01.052 --> 00:37:03.021
Dr. Rudnick only
became a suspect

768
00:37:03.121 --> 00:37:06.250
based on false accusations
by serial killer Greg Yates.

769
00:37:06.658 --> 00:37:09.560
in a desperate attempt to throw
doubt on his own conviction.

770
00:37:09.661 --> 00:37:10.685
Even if that's true.

771
00:37:10.795 --> 00:37:12.696
I'm sure the State
would not waste my time

772
00:37:12.797 --> 00:37:14.629
if they didn't have more
compelling evidence.

773
00:37:14.933 --> 00:37:18.768
Dr. Rudnick. you are to surrender
your passport to the court.

774
00:37:18.870 --> 00:37:20.771
Bail is set at $2 million.

775
00:37:20.872 --> 00:37:21.872
(GAVEL BANGS)

776
00:37:21.940 --> 00:37:23.374
(SIGHS)

777
00:37:23.975 --> 00:37:26.069
Rudnick posted
a $2 million bail?

778
00:37:26.177 --> 00:37:27.975
There's no money
like family money.

779
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:30.310
It was wired in before
he was even processed.

780
00:37:30.448 --> 00:37:33.441
Hey. Check this out.
"The ME Nobody Knows."

781
00:37:34.185 --> 00:37:35.710
"The Monster in the Morgue."

782
00:37:35.820 --> 00:37:38.187
I mean. these headlines.
they write themselves.

783
00:37:38.289 --> 00:37:39.780
It's a freaky story.

784
00:37:39.891 --> 00:37:41.985
Yeah. Getting
freakier by the minute...

785
00:37:43.528 --> 00:37:46.760
Mommy and Noah will get a little
time later. There you go. sweetie.

786
00:37:47.298 --> 00:37:49.460
Okay. All right. Love you.

787
00:37:49.567 --> 00:37:51.487
ROLLINS: Hey. Sarge.
you're gonna wanna see this.

788
00:37:52.270 --> 00:37:53.761
Great. You got something?

789
00:37:53.872 --> 00:37:57.240
Yeah. Facial recognition
came back on that TSA photo.

790
00:37:57.342 --> 00:37:59.072
It's definitely not Lena.

791
00:37:59.177 --> 00:38:02.238
Yeah. the jawline is wide by two
centimeters. the symmetry is wrong.

792
00:38:02.347 --> 00:38:04.475
And they also say it's not
inconsistent with Rudnick.

793
00:38:04.582 --> 00:38:07.279
This guy has a closet full of wigs
and dresses. We know it's him.

794
00:38:07.385 --> 00:38:09.547
We may know it's Rudnick.
but Barba wants proof.

795
00:38:09.654 --> 00:38:12.249
We need that photo of Lena in
Switzerland that he sent to Susie.

796
00:38:12.357 --> 00:38:14.917
Well. I've been trying to
reach Susie. So far no luck.

797
00:38:15.059 --> 00:38:17.858
All right. Rollins.
let's call Yates. Now.

798
00:38:18.530 --> 00:38:20.499
Something happened to Susie.

799
00:38:20.598 --> 00:38:22.226
She was supposed
to call this morning.

800
00:38:22.467 --> 00:38:24.060
She would never just forget.

801
00:38:24.202 --> 00:38:25.795
When's the last time
you talked to her?

802
00:38:25.937 --> 00:38:28.532
YATES: <i>Last night. She
said she had good news.</i>

803
00:38:28.640 --> 00:38:29.640
"Good news"?

804
00:38:29.707 --> 00:38:31.539
She said that she
had found the photo

805
00:38:31.643 --> 00:38:33.771
that Lena supposedly
sent from Switzerland.

806
00:38:33.878 --> 00:38:36.712
She felt it looked a
lot like Rudnick in drag.

807
00:38:37.949 --> 00:38:39.349
Was she gonna tell Rudnick that?

808
00:38:39.450 --> 00:38:40.816
<i>No. I don't think so.</i>

809
00:38:42.086 --> 00:38:43.987
<i>Wait. he's still in
custody. isn't he?</i>

810
00:38:44.756 --> 00:38:46.520
No. he made bail last night.

811
00:38:48.159 --> 00:38:49.159
Oh. no.

812
00:38:51.629 --> 00:38:53.495
(SIRENS WAILING)

813
00:38:53.598 --> 00:38:54.657
She's not here?

814
00:38:54.766 --> 00:38:56.632
No. And I doubt she
went along willingly.

815
00:39:01.239 --> 00:39:02.239
(DOOR CLOSES)

816
00:39:11.416 --> 00:39:13.544
Blood's mostly dried.
It's been a while.

817
00:39:15.153 --> 00:39:17.281
Get a BOLO out on Rudnick. ASAP.

818
00:39:17.755 --> 00:39:19.587
Then head over
to Real Time Crime.

819
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:21.785
We're gonna need
a task force. TARU.

820
00:39:21.893 --> 00:39:24.021
TSA. Port Authority
Police. You know the drill.

821
00:39:24.128 --> 00:39:25.255
On it.

822
00:39:25.630 --> 00:39:27.656
Hey. Sarge. Sarge.

823
00:39:27.765 --> 00:39:29.965
I might have heard something
come over the borough-wide.

824
00:39:30.235 --> 00:39:32.602
Got freshly cut body parts
coming in with the tide.

825
00:39:32.704 --> 00:39:35.367
"Cut"? Were they female?

826
00:39:37.342 --> 00:39:38.342
(SIGHS)

827
00:39:42.046 --> 00:39:43.207
What do we have?

828
00:39:43.314 --> 00:39:45.977
Well. we're still putting
the pieces together.

829
00:39:46.117 --> 00:39:49.451
Some fishermen saw the bags
coming in about an hour ago.

830
00:39:49.554 --> 00:39:50.831
SONNY: And this
is why I hate fishing.

831
00:39:50.855 --> 00:39:52.066
Learned that growing
up in Staten Island.

832
00:39:52.090 --> 00:39:54.218
We're a long way from Elmhurst.

833
00:39:55.326 --> 00:39:57.227
We're not sure it's Susie.

834
00:40:13.645 --> 00:40:14.977
We are now.

835
00:40:19.984 --> 00:40:20.984
(EXHALES)

836
00:40:31.696 --> 00:40:33.665
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
